The DA criticized Health MEC Qedani Mahlangu for failing to resign over &#8216;her negligence&#8217; regarding the deaths of 37 psychiatric patients. JOHANNESBURG - The Democratic Alliance (DA) in Gauteng has called on Premier David Makhura to take action against Health MEC Qedani Mahlangu, saying that she is not fit to hold office.The party presented the 2016 Gauteng Cabinet score cards at the provincial legislature earlier on Wednesday, where they ranked Mahlangu 0 out of 10.They criticized her for failing to resign over what they called her negligence regarding the deaths of 37 psychiatric patients who were moved from the Life Healthcare Esidimeni facility. DA Gauteng leader John Moodey says: She should ve resigned if she really wanted to be remorseful for her actions, especially since she d been warned that there could be ramifications or negative outcome if she continued to do what she has done. Her continued divergence on the subject and defiance on the matter makes her appear more complaisant then a simple bystander in a failed project. LISTEN: MEC for Health Qedani Mahlangu on the deaths of 36 psychiatric patientsRadio 702 | Talk Radio 702's John Robbie imterviews Health MEC Qedani Mahlangu following the deaths of 36 psychiatric patients in Gauteng. CAPE TOWN - The deaths of 36 psychiatric patients in Gauteng has raised concerns. Health MEC Qedani Mahlangu says her department has launched a probe into the deaths.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)